originalText: Use the western dock. Everythin' else is off-limits.
Yer late. Get movin' and unload the stuff. Just unload it here on the dock and our workers will bring it in. Don't go wanderin' off unless yer lookin' for trouble, ya dig?
Um, what do you mean by "wanderin' off"?
I'm not looking for trouble: I'm bringing trouble. ::Attack!::
What the-- Hold it right there!
Hey! HEY! Ya ain't supposed to be 'ere!
Hey you - *you*, come 'ere. ::He takes a good look at you.:: Haven't seen yer face 'round 'ere before.
Are ya stupid or what? Everythin' but this dock is off-limits. *Off-limits*. That means ya get shot if we find ya snoopin' around. Ya dig now?
I got my eyes on ya.
Keep yer hands where I can see 'em.
If I see ya doin' anythin' suspicious...
Yer on Black Eel territory now, $(#jack/sis).
Make sure to visit the tavern.
If ya need somethin' for yer jet: Boulder's Jet Bits. Right by the tavern.
Murky, the tavern keeper, also sells ammo if ya need some.
If I catch ya fiddlin' with anyone's jet...
The recent pirate raid was just an isolated incident. These waters still belong to us.
We're already makin' the stinkin' pirates pay for Armstrong. We're killin' them by the dozens.
What are ya waitin' for? Advance payment?
Come on, we ain't got all day!
Who're you? Ya ain't supposed to be 'ere.
First time seein' you 'ere. Whaddya want?
What if I need to take a leak?
::[Persuade]:: I'm the new $(#guy/girl). Came here to figure out why the system's been running slow lately.

::[Persuade][Hacking]:: I'm the new $(#guy/girl). Came here to check out the slowdowns you've been experiencing lately. Now considering you're running advanced military software on that crappy-looking laptop... Eh, could be anything: CPU overheating, hard drive issues, viruses or just some background app doing crap. Anyway, the sooner I start the sooner I get 'er back up to full speed.
Anyone ever told ya ya, uh... look a lot like the Invictus?
Heard about the raid? Them pirates are at it again!
Heard about, uh... what the pirates did to Protectorate? Holy pentapus!
::[Persuade]:: I'm the new $(#guy/girl). Been told you $(#folks needed an extra pair of hands/boys needed some help) around here, so here I am earning myself some shinies.
Silas sent me. I got something for the boss.
Sorry, but I really gotta rush.

What the-- Then take it in yer pants, dammit! I don't give a rat's. With the kind of raids the pirates've been pullin' off lately, we ain't takin' chances with anythin' or anyone. For all I know, there could be a band of 'em hidin' in that container right there, ready to slice my throat wide open.

Just... just keep to this dock, $(#jack/sis), and we're cool. Dig?
::He raises his weapon.:: Thought ya could fool me, punk?
Not so fast! ::He raises his weapon.::
::Feel the bottle.:: Got a colder one?
::[Perception]:: All the wiring seems to be leading here. Is that the power room?
::[Intelligence]:: All the wiring seems to be leading here. Is that the power room?
::[Persuade]:: I'm the new $(#guy/girl). We're doin' some work on the turrets and need to turn 'em off for about half an hour or so.

::[Persuade][Electronics]:: I'm the new $(#guy/girl). We got some turrets workin' sluggish, so I came 'ere  to turn off the power so we could try an' figure out what's causin' the low voltage. The network's not overloaded, we checked that first, an' wirin' looks good. Frankly, I'm just hopin' it's not the bloody transformer.

Silas? Silas is dead, ya dumb bastard!

WE GOT AN INTRUDER!
For the rigmaster? Give it 'ere. I'll bring it to 'im.
Uh... Yeah. Mike'll be 'ere shortly to give ya a hand. He's the one workin' with the thing. He, uh... went to rest 'is eyes.
Colder? ::He presses the bottle against his cheek.:: It's as cold as freakin' cryogel!

::He hands you the brew.:: 

So, uh... how's it goin'? Figured out what's buggin' it?
Yeah... uh... I'll letcha do yer thing.

Well, ya better shut up 'n' do yers, alright. 

Ungrateful bastard...
::He smiles.:: Hey, that's awesome! Ya know, that thing's, uh... really important.
That's right. Now answer my question.
::[Intimidate]:: If this was intended for your grubby fingers to defile, you would've known by now.
::[Persuade]:: No can do, man. I was told not to show, much less hand this over to anyone but the rigmaster himself.
Let the man rest: I'm here.
As a matter of fact yes, yes I did.
I know, I know. That's why I came all the way here, buddy. ::Smile.::
Now who are you 'n' whaddya want?
I ain't diggin' nuthin' of whatcha sayin'.
Hey, ya watch yer tongue, you!
Yeah, alright. Should be back soon anyway.

::He stares at you, and soon frowns.::

Ya almost fooled me, ya crapper! ::He lunges at you with his knife.::
Awesome. So... ya fixed it, right?
::He nods a few times in understanding, as if you've told him something profound.::
Hey, why ain't it glowin' no more? Them lights used to be always on.
Just go in 'n' do yer thing.

Okay, okay, ya can go. Go on through.

::He mutters to himself.:: Bloody bastards never tellin' me nothin'...
Oh, and... could you please get me a cold brew? Helps my brain do them calculations right. Thanks.
I certanly did. Now I really...
It's rebooting. They'll be on in a couple of minutes.
They were drawing way too much power, so I switched them off. They were causing the slowdowns, in fact.

::[Electronics] or [Hacking]:: Had to switch them off. They were drawing way too much power, and the aging power supply unit was struggling to deliver the needed voltage, which in turn raises the current so that the power can remain constant, which in turn raises the temperature due to resistance, which finally results in the cpu slowing down as to avoid damage.
They'll turn on in a few minutes.
Who cares about the lights, man?
Uh... okay. I'll tell Mike whatcha did.
Y-ya broke it, ya dumb crapper! ::He grabs his head.:: Do ya even g-g-gotta clue whatcha did, ya... ya...!
Well... carry on, then. In case ya haven't been told: Steer clear of the northwestern section. That's off-limits, dig?
Heh, it's even runnin' a lot quieter than before.
Sure is. Now I really gotta go. So long.

Yeah, yeah, bye.

Can't wait to hear what Mike's gonna say...
